4. Irreversibility
Collapse cannot be averaged away.
Without irreversibility, moral hazard enters immediately.

5. Independent Witness Principle (Trias Testium)
Truth must survive disagreement.
Without this, consensus becomes political.

6. Absence Defaults to Failure
Uncertainty must tighten constraint.
Without this, silence becomes exploitation.
Verdict
These six form the ontological spine.
They define what truth means inside the system.

